Package: okBATHTUB
Title: Reservoir Eutrophication Modeling for Oklahoma Lakes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jordon", "Henderson",
           email = "jordon.henderson@owrb.ok.gov",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "")),
    person("Oklahoma Water Resources Board", role = "cph")
  )
Description: Implements steady-state empirical reservoir water quality modeling
    based on Walker's BATHTUB framework (Walker 1996), extended with
    Oklahoma-specific calibration options for lakes in the OWRB Lake Monitoring
    Program. Predicts in-lake total phosphorus, total nitrogen, chlorophyll-a,
    and Secchi depth from tributary nutrient and hydraulic loading inputs, and
    computes Carlson (1977) Trophic State Indices. Supports single-segment and
    multi-segment reservoir configurations, load reduction scenario analysis,
    and optional integration with OWRB AWQMS water quality data. Designed to
    complement watershed loading models such as OK-HAWQS/SWAT in a two-model
    nutrient management workflow.
